This paper is primarily focused on the problem of checking consistency models in transactional databases, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which involves analyzing the computational complexity of different consistency models, and devising algorithms to solve the problem efficiently. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-categories of distributed computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
